node.text: We're back in @amandahesser's kitchen, and today, she's making fall-off-the-bone ribs that are sure to score serious points at your next barbeque. They get slathered in a rub mixture of sea salt, paprika, ground coffee beans, and peppercorns, then slow-cooked for 7 hours (for maximum flavor!). Grab Resident @ladyandpups's recipe for Coffee-Crusted Barbecue Beef Ribs at the link in bio. #f52community
